      "content": "The shame you feel is a heavy and isolating thing, but it's a feeling, not a permanent truth about who you are. The perception of failure is often much louder in our minds than it is in reality. Allow yourself to acknowledge the depth of this pain without judgment, because you are going through something incredibly traumatic. If you can, try to speak to someone safe about this intense feeling of being exposed.",
      "source": "target",
