      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's what i don't get. how can it be \"just a feeling\" when it's my whole reality? every time i think about walking into my parents' house or even just looking at my old colleagues, i feel like I'm dying inside. it's like this crushing pressure that never stops. sometimes i just think... if i didn't have to deal with the look on their faces, if i didn't have to live with this disgrace, it would all just be quiet. wouldn't it be easier if the shame just... stopped?",
